<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=telurinon>Telurinon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/13/03 8:37 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Perception of the Wizards groupability.</span><hr size=1> It's pretty obvious (to me at least) that wizards need something unique that they can add to a group, but that fits with the feel and theme of the class as well.<br>
<br>
So, how about a line of spells that operate sort of like Haste but as damage instead of speed?  Haste increases speed with which a melee type can attack, creating faster DPS.  This hypothetical spell line would add bane damage of either Fire or Cold depending on the spell and it's level to a melee type.<br>
<br>
Progression could go something like this:<br>
<br>
Level 4: +1 Fire, single target short duration (2 minutes?)<br>
Level 8: +1 Cold, single target, short duration (longer duration than level 4 [3 minutes])<br>
Level 12: +1 Fire, group buff, short duration<br>
Level 16: +1 Cold, group buff, short duration<br>
Level 20: +2 Fire, Single Target, short duration<br>
etc. with high end versions adding up to +5 damage or a +3 damage with a very long duration (you know, to make money with!)<br>
<br>
Thoughts?  Would a spell line like this overpower melee making them too strong vs. current content?  Would it achieve the goal of making wizards more group friendly?<br>
 <p><img src=http://home.socal.rr.com/fgrubb/images/Misc/tel_flame.gif><br><SELECT NAME=D1<br><OPTION SELECTED>Telurinon Aelvenborne, 55th Rake of Black Isle<br><OPTION>Mangore Orcsplitter, 41st Warrior of Black Isle<OPTION>Dewin gan'Bran, 48th Wizard of Black Isle<br></SELECT><br><font color=#80FFFF><I>Skating away on the thin ice of a new day.</I></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=carighanmaconar01>CarighanMaconar01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/14/03 6:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Perception of the Wizards groupability.</span><hr size=1> I don't know, adding new stuff is simply source of more balancing discussion, may it be from wizards, or may it be from whoever else. The main problem of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>most</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> classes with grouping problem <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">is</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> the perception of the other players. Crits help there, but in my oppinion, spell damage should have it's own filter, much like you can see melee damage if you want.<br>
<br>
Now, a wizard may not bring the high DPS of a Mage to a group, but his ability to &quot;burn&quot; down mobs is what i value when i take Wizards into my groups. It can help greatly in emergency situations - and if it too fails, a wizard can still evac the entire group <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The problem is that Clerics CH, Shamans Slow, Druids SoW and do PotG, Enchanters KEI, Mezz and Charm, Necromancers FD, do undead form and have a pet, Mages have a pet and summon - all lasting experiences since you (as another player) see them <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">all</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> the time they are used - wizards don't have such a thing besides evac...<br>
<br>
Which indeed poses problems with finding groups, since many players refuse to learn the details of another class then those they play themselves... <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55795">Carighan Maconar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Enchantress of the 59th Circle<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Member of the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.nebelwelt.de/eq/index.htm">Namenlose Bruderschaft</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> on Solusek Ro<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.mutedfaith.com/quiz/qz4.htm&quot;" target="&quot;new&quot;"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mutedfaith.com/images/time.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.mutedfaith.com/quiz/qz4.htm&quot;" target="&quot;new&quot;">find your element</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> at <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.mutedfaith.com&quot;" target="&quot;new&quot;">mutedfaith.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luxum>Luxum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Pics plz thx :(</span><br>  Posts: 2072<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/14/03 8:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Perception of the Wizards groupability.</span><hr size=1> It helps a lot when the enchanter insists on having a wizzie!  Hardly anyone will argue with the enchanter!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   And we are real handy for rooting and snaring mezzed mobs for you.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :grinyes --><img src=http://graffes.netfirms.com/smiley/yes.gif ALT=":grinyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=targonis>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 734<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/15/03 9:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoP</span><hr size=1> Perception really IS the main problem that wizards have, and it's not because ALL wizards have poor damage output, but because people can't see by looking how good a wizard is.  The TYPICAL wizard of a given level is a LOT less powerful than the TYPICAL melee of a given level.<br>
<br>
AA skills are where most of the power of a wizard comes from, not from just being a given level.  People can get to level 65 as a wizard by soloing, but they may not have a single big nuke, and without KNOWING the wizard in question, it's a big question mark about how effective the wizard will be.<br>
<br>
Spell Casting Mastery 3 to let us cast more spells before running out of mana for example, or how many AA points we have put into crits(spell casting fury, spell casting fury mastery, Fury of Magic Mastery).  How about spells?  Getting Agnarr's or Strike of Solusek boost our damage output in a major way, even in XP groups if we are careful about agro.  Others just can't SEE where we've put our AA points, there's a minor way to tell, is someone a baron, master, or sage, but who knows how you spent your points, you could have done mental clarity to get to master/mistress).  People also can't see our spell list to see if we have the DPS improving nukes and AAs.<br>
<br>
THAT in my opinion is the key.  You can just LOOK at a melee, and see if they have poor equipment, you can see the equipment on a caster, but equipment except for focus effects and flowing thoughts, don't really do much for us.  Verant needs to realize this and make inspect give that information.  Even for melees, being able to inspect a melee and get their AC and ATK would be helpful.  In mostly single player games like Dungeon Siege, buffs have a visible effect, you can see when someone has an effect on them, even if it's a bit of a glow.  EQ doesn't have this.  You can't tell if the equipment someone has are weak junk, or very powerful.  You can inspect someone, but we'd still need to request that the person link their items, and that's a pain.  It may not be realistic to be able to see the numbers directly, but character ABILITY is secondary to equipment for melees.  For casters, character equipment is secondary to ability.  I'm not talking how skilled the players are, I'm talking the character.  AAs and spells are character abilities.  But what new skills do melees get?  A melee with good equipment and few AA skills is still considered a useful tank, a caster with good equipment and few AA skills is considered weak.<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 65 Wizard<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
