</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faramir42>Faramir42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/3/03 10:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoP</span><hr size=1> Perception is EVERYTHING. It doesn't matter what you really meant, or intended. If someone perceives it one way, to them that is the way it is.<br>
<br>
Yes, wizards are percieved as a solo class. To me, that is a wrong perception, since, there are no solo classes in the game, since the game is not designed to be played solo. Now everyone flame me about that. Yes, some classes can solo better. However, since no single class, can solo EVERY where, or EVERY mob in the game, that is why I say their is no truely solo class. And Sony/Verant never made a solo game, they made a multi player game. <br>
<br>
People are silly in their perceptions. Using the new LFG feature, I sent a tell to someone. The response I got was, Oh, we have a wizard. Um, hello, two wizards are better then one. <br>
<br>
People can't see what wizards do. All melees that I know have other peoples damage on, so they can messure how much damage they are doing compared to themselve. It's a vainty, yes. So I agree, they need to change it so that damage from spells shows up on other people's screen. Having it say &quot;A moss snake skins blisters from magical fire for 250 damage&quot; would make people see what we are doing. <br>
<br>
Often when grouped with less knowledgable melees, they always think they are doing ALL the damage or most of it. <br>
<br>
I don't get aggro alot or often not at all. Many peoples perception of wizards are aggro magnets. Why? Because often it is true. They want to prove thier usefullness, so they start nuking right away, get aggro, run around screaming help help get it off me, the tank only gets aggro back cause the wizard died. Great, rez, wait, med, wait, tank wants to fight. Standing around doesn't get me the xp I need thinks the warrior. Wizards, DON'T RUN if you get aggro. Running does not stop you from getting hit. Getting hit from behind often means more damage. If you don't think so, try it. Stand right behind or next to the tank and cast if you are always getting aggro. The tank will be able to get aggro back before you die. <br>
<br>
Enchanters are just as much an aggro magnet, even more so then wizards. Only what they can do is measureable and visible. Wizards, cast your DS on the tank without being asked to. You will soon see them asking for it. Why? even though it's your spell, they will think it's damage they are doing. They will say, Oh man, that was awesome! everytime I got hit I did 5 points of damage! the thing was beating it self to death! Melees' LOVE DS, so give them your's. And if your going up against fire using creatures, they will have a higher FR. Also, giving melee's your DS means that everytime they get hit, they do damage, they increase thier aggro with the mob. That means the melees, aggro is going up faster. Which means you are less likely to pull aggro. So don't think of DS as damage, but as aggro for the melee.<br>
<br>
Most people's experience with wizards is watching them die. And if a wizard is dying, unless the group really sucks, it's only the wizards fault. For most groups, a wizard means evac. If they don't have an evacer, they stay near the zone and fight so they can zone quickly. <br>
<br>
It's up to each wizard to change a persons perception.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faramir42>Faramir42</A> at: 3/3/03 10:25:51 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=enoah35>Enoah35</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 626<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/4/03 4:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoP</span><hr size=1> Faramir42:<br>
